body:
So I was rewatching Infinity War, and Strange flat out says “We’re in the ENDGAME now.” To Tony after he asks why Strange gave Thanos the stone.

And I have honestly never been more disappointed in myself for not picking up such a major clue for the title. They literally told us in the movie…. smh.

summary: I noticed something
body:
I noticed something

The FFH trailer has a moment where Flash says something about Iron Man, and you see this glimpse of Peter like 🤔 and then it cuts away to MJ when she says “what is it with you and spiderman” and you see Peter in a totally different spot, back behind the stairs texting someone-

So my thought is, you know, people are saying he seems too happy for Iron Man to be dead, but yall gotta remember: peter parker is a gen z teenager who likely suppresses his emotions if their too painful- especially if his senses are heightened. So what if he hears the name Iron Man and he kind of just slinks away to text Aunt May about it. What if that’s why he’s looking at the suit with so much of a sad face. It’s why Happy is telling him he’s alone. Fml.
